âœª Types of Consistency:

â†’ Strong Consistency:
1ï¸âƒ£  Also known as linearizability or strict consistency.
2ï¸âƒ£  Guarantees every read operation receives the most recent write or an error.ğŸ”
3ï¸âƒ£  Requires coordination between nodes, impacting performance and availability.âš™ï¸
